{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 200°C. Dust a baking tray with flour then set aside.","Place plain flour, wholemeal flour, salt and bicarbonate of soda in mixing bowl then mix <nobr>5 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>.","Add buttermilk and mix <nobr>25 sec\/speed 5.5<\/nobr>. Working quickly, tip the sticky dough out onto a floured surface and bring together into a ball. Place on prepared tray.","Dust loaf with flour then, with a floured sharp knife cut a cross in the top of dough about 3 cm deep. Bake for 25-35 minutes (200°C) until loaf sounds hollow when tapped underneath. Transfer to a wire rack to cool before serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["250 g plain flour, plus extra for dusting","250 g wholemeal flour","1 ½ tsp fine sea salt","1 ½ tsp bicarbonate of soda","450 g buttermilk"]}],"id":"r92997","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-xhlFxWZe0wU\/XZaongPh3aI\/AAAAAAAAhL4\/Fv2Nzq7x13IBjV_1-fwcKrv4FClk4mTVQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_tkxP1rLHf5J9onEZ.png","title":"Irish Soda Bread","publishedAt":"2015-12-17T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"4.8 g","fat":"0.6 g","uom":"per 1 slice","carbohydrates":"24.9 g","calories":"521 kJ \/ 125 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking tray, long sharp knife, wire rack, oven, oven","hintsAndTricks":["This tasty, slightly sweet, crumbly cake-like bread is really quick to make, thanks to the baking soda which is used as a leavening agent instead of yeast. There are several variations of soda bread to be found throughout different regions of Ireland - we’ve gone for a mixture of plain and wholemeal flours. A perfect accompaniment to a big bowl of steaming soup or simply enjoyed buttered with jam or lemon curd."],"basicInfo":["easy","5m","45m","16 slices"]}